cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Hi Everyone and welcome to today's Precision Club session, in which the plan is that we'll be continuing our look at sequences over a 1NT Opening.

The topic today is not "Precision-specific" in that what I'm going to deal with could apply equally to ACOL, Standard American, 2/1 or any other system.

Consequently, don't be afraid to sit and play (later in the session) if you not yet "into" Precision, although the example hands do assume a VARIABLE 1NT Opening (10-12 Non-vul and 13-15 Vul).

Similarly, the scheme of responses that you play over a Precision Opening 1NT bid does not really affect any part of the system, and so you are free to use whatever scheme of responses you like.

What I am going to show you today is simply my preferred scheme.

I don't, for example, claim that what I suggest you play in these sessions is necessarily "better" than other methods, but I would make a bit of an exception for the  ^*b2-way 2@D^*n  response I'm going to show you tonight.

Coupled with non-promissory Stayman and 4-suit transfers, it provides methods for getting to the right contract that I've never found anywhere else.

If you have not already done so, please have a look at the notes I have prepared on Precision Club bidding.

You can find these on: ^p^*hhttp://ocp.pigpen.org.uk^*n

The Notes on 1NT Sequences can be found at:^p^*hhttp://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/1n.php^*n

