cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  First, as it is highly pertinent, a recap of last week's session:  
^^
We covered  ^*b1NT,  Stayman^*n  and  ^*b4-way Transfers^*n.

Because  1NT - 2@S  is a transfer to @C and  1NT - 2NT  is a transfer to Diamonds, balanced invitations to 3NT HAVE to go VIA Stayman, so  1NT - 2@C  does NOT promise a 4-card Major.

Thus the sequence  1NT - 2@C - 2x - 2NT  may or may not contain a 4-card Major.

So, if responder has an invitational hand 4-card Spades but no Hearts, and the sequence starts  1NT - 2@C - 2@H, then Responder has to now bid  2@S  to show the Spades rather than 2NT.

But  1NT - 2@C - 2@H - 3NT  still promises 4-card Spades, (because there's be no point using Stayman otherwise).

As we'll see during this week's Session, invitations that go via Stayman only want to be in game if Opener is a bursting MAXIMUM for their 1NT Opener (ie: they are only a MILD invitation).

We'll deal with STRONG invitations this week (ones where we want to be in game if Opener is anything better than a rock-bottom MINIMUM).


^*bTransfers (recap):^*n a Transfer then a bid of a new suit is always game-forcing.

1NT - 2@D      Transfer to @HHearts@H     ^*bOR^*n     a balanced invitation (2-way 2@D), covered this session    
1NT - 2@H      Transfer to @SSpades@S
1NT - 2@S      Transfer to @CClubs@C
1NT - 2NT    Transfer to @DDiamonds@D

With 2 suits you transfer into the longest  OR   (if even-suited) high-ranking of the two  and then bid the other one.
