|cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|   If Opener completes the transfer to 2@H and responder now bids 2@S then this 
^c@2
@.   completely CANCELS OUT the transfer

@.   is 100% artificial, says NOTHING about  SPADES

@.   shows a hand worth AT LEAST a STRONG invitation to 3NT, (one wanting to be in 3NT if Opener 
^eis better than minimum)  but can be  ^*ba lot stronger^*n  than that.
^b@2

Using this method, the hands that bid  2@D over 1NT  fall into one of the following categories:- 
^c@2
(1)   Any hand with 5-card or longer Hearts (and no longer suit),  a normal transfer hand.

(2)   Any hand that wants to be in Game if partner is BETTER THAN MINIMUM 
^d(in 3NT or a suit, depending on finding a 4-4 fit, of course).

(3)   Any hand without a 5-card suit potentially or definitely interested in a slam of some sort.
^b@2

The secret behind this method is a similar principle to transfers, in that the 2@S rebid simply asks if Opener is minimum, or BETTER THAN minimum.

If  ^*bminimum^*n, Opener rebids  ^*b2NT^*n,         ^*bANY^*n    other bid shows   ^*bbetter than minimum^*n.

The point is that when Opener shows a minimum hand, responder is in a position to continue if they wish, because we have effectively transferred to 2NT.
