nt|^z@3^b@2|at|^^^^|
cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  The 2-way 2@D works with ANY strength 1NT Opening and ANY system.

The only "cost" in using it is losing one round of bidding when Responder has a slam-going Major 2-suiter with longer Hearts.

Used appropriately, it's an invaluable additional to our 1NT arsenal, more flexible than Minor-suit Stayman and allows us to explore for slam values at the 2-level rather than having to bid a quantitative 4NT, and STILL be able to try to find a fit in a Major OR a Minor whether Opener is minimum or maximum.

The combination of non-promissory Stayman, 4-suit transfers and the 2-way 2@D has been extensively used and tested over 30 years and I've never found any alternative method that consistently gives as good results.
